   <concept id="FAR_42_1501"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.1501</ph> General.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2547e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2573e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Past performance information (including
the ratings and supporting narratives) is relevant information,
for future source selection purposes, regarding a contractor’s actions
under previously awarded contracts or orders. It includes, for example,
the contractor’s record of-</p>
               <ol id="d2547e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Conforming
to requirements and to standards of good workmanship;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e21" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Forecasting
and controlling costs;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e26" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Adherence
to schedules, including the administrative aspects of performance;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e31" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Reasonable
and cooperative behavior and commitment to customer satisfaction;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2021-07 September 10, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-004?>Complying
with the requirements of the small business subcontracting plan
(see <xref href="19.705-7.dita#FAR_19_705_7"
                                 base="i1100497"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">19.705-7</xref>(b));<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 42.1501 by redesignating paragraphs (a)(5) thru (a)(7) as paragraphs (a)(6) thru (a)(8) and adding a new paragraph (a)(5).?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e47" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph> Reporting
into databases (see subpart <xref href="Subpart_4.14.dita#FAR_Subpart_4_14"
                              base="i1121746"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">4.14</xref>, and reporting requirements
in the solicitation provisions and clauses referenced in <xref href="9.104-7.dita#FAR_9_104_7"
                              base="i1116212"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">9.104-7</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e58" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph> Integrity
and business ethics; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2573e63" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(8)</ph> Business-like
concern for the interest of the customer.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2573e68" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Agencies
shall monitor their compliance with the past performance evaluation
requirements (see <xref href="42.1502.dita#FAR_42_1502"
                        base="i1074248"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">42.1502</xref>),
and use the Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System (CPARS)
metric tools to measure the quality and timely reporting of past
performance information. CPARS is the official source for past performance
information.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
